						               													<description>Using the latest genetic technologies, you will fulfill your dream of creating a cretaceous park! To do so, you will place dinosaurs in your park to attract tourists. But be aware of rival parks, attacks will be constant! Who will get more tourists?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player starts with a hand of three dinosaur cards. There are two common stacks: one for dinosaurs and another one for tourists.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players will make turns and in their turn they will follow these two steps:&amp;#10;1.Draw one card: a dinosaur or a tourist.&amp;#10;2.Do one action choosing between these two options:&amp;#10; 2a.Expand your park by placing one dinosaur in it.&amp;#10; 2b.Attack and steal one dinosaur from another park using one stronger dinosaur from your hand, which will be discarded afterwards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When you get two dinosaurs of the same type in your park, a tourist will come to see them and give you profits so you can take another dinosaur card from the common stack.&amp;#10;When you get three dinosaurs of the same type in your park, you can place a Ranger that will protect dinosaurs and tourists in that group.&amp;#10;When you get four dinosaurs of the same type in your park, you can steal a tourist from another park.&amp;#10;After an attack, if a carnivorous dinosaur is left without a partner it will eat its tourist which goes to his owners' hand. The tourist also goes to his owners hand when the last herbivorous dinosaur from a group is lost.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When both common dinosaur and tourist stacks are depleted, a last round is played and then the game ends. The park with more tourists is the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-description from designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
